					<p>Branded as Biosafe Train, the new safety kit is an offshoot of an ongoing project in East Africa that has its sights on ensuring safety in biotechnology and the ecology through capacity building on risk assessment. According to the Biosafe Train coordinator, understanding the risks and opportunities that shroud the cultivation of GMOs is likely to narrow the rift created by pro and anti GMO lobbyists and present the farmer with an opportunity to make informed choices (Source: David Njagi, Africa Science News Service, 29 October 2008).</p>
