					<p>Experts drawn from Kenya Agricultural Research Institute (KARI) and their counterparts from the International Maize and Wheat Improvement Centre (CIMMYT) are expected to make a major announcement towards this at a workshop set to mark the end of phase 2 of the Insect Resistant Maize for Africa Project that is close to a decade today. The announcement will unveil a new maize variety with significant resistance to attack by the LGB in storage bins (Source: George Kebasso, Africa Science News Service, 27 October 2008).</p>
